{"title_page": "Slow Burn (podcast)", "text_new": "{{short description|Podcast}}\n{{Infobox podcast\n| show_name = Slow Burn\n| title = Slow Burn\n| image = Slow_Burn_podcast.jpg\n| format = {{hlist|[[History]]|[[Drama]]|Political Commentary}}\n| runtime = Typically 20 to 30 minutes\n| producer = Andrew Parsons\n| host = \n| starring = [[Leon Neyfakh]]\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| first_aired = November 28, 2017\n| num_episodes = {{plainlist|\n*Main series: 23<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|title=Slow Burn|url=https://slate.com/podcasts/slow-burn/s3/biggie-and-tupac|work=Slate Magazine}}</ref>\n*Bonus: 7}}\n| website = [https://slate.com/podcasts/slow-burn/s3/biggie-and-tupac] or visit [https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/slow-burn-a-podcast-about-watergate/id1315040130]\n}}\n'''''Slow Burn''''' is a narrative podcast produced by Slate Plus, a division of ''[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]].'' The first two seasons of the podcast are hosted by [[Leon Neyfakh]]<ref name=\"auto\" />; the third season of the show, released in 2019, is hosted by Joel Anderson<ref>{{Cite web|title='Slow Burn' Season 3 Turns Its Investigative Eye To The Murders Of Biggie And Tupac|url=https://www.npr.org/2019/11/07/776908450/slow-burn-season-3-turns-its-investigative-eye-to-the-murders-of-biggie-and-tupa|work=NPR.org|access-date=2019-11-17|language=en}}</ref>.\n\nThe first season is about the [[Watergate scandal]] featuring interviews with [[Bob Woodward]] among others.\n\nThe second is about the [[Impeachment of Bill Clinton]] featuring an interview with [[Linda Tripp]], among others.\n\nThe third season covers the growing tension between rappers [[Tupac Shakur]] and [[The Notorious B.I.G.|The Notorious B.I.G]]. in the 1990s<ref>{{Cite web|last=Anderson|first=Joel|title=Slow Burn|url=https://slate.com/podcasts/slow-burn/s3/biggie-and-tupac|work=Slate Magazine|date=2019-10-29|access-date=2019-11-17|language=en}}</ref>. \n\nThe podcast premiered on November 28, 2017 and became \"one of the top shows on Apple Podcasts.\"<ref name=\"usatoday.com\">{{cite web|title=Have you heard 'Slow Burn'? Slate's Watergate podcast is hot right now|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/12/02/slow-burn-slate-podcast-watergate/912144001/|work=}}</ref>\n\n==Reviews==\n''Slow Burn'' received a positive review from ''Vulture''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Slow Burn Is the Watergate Podcast You Didn\u2019t Know You Needed\n|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/01/podcast-review-slow-burn.html|accessdate=2019-12-16}}</ref> ''USA Today'' named ''Slow Burn'' as a \"hot\" recommended podcast.<ref name=\"usatoday.com\"/> ''The New York Times'' praised ''Slow Burn'' and credited [[Malcolm Gladwell]] with leading the way by making historic podcasts that focused on neglected aspects of well known events, like ''Slow Burn'', possible.<ref>{{cite web|title=Archived copy|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/15/arts/podcasts-revisionist-history-malcolm-gladwell.html/|accessdate=2018-02-04|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180203070053/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/15/arts/podcasts-revisionist-history-malcolm-gladwell.html|archivedate=2018-02-03}}</ref>\n\n==TV adaptation==\nIt was announced in February 2019 that [[Epix]] is producing a six-part television series based on the first season Watergate investigation. It premiered on February 16, 2020.<ref>https://www.theverge.com/2019/2/10/18219436/epix-slate-slow-burn-podcast-documentary-series</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bennett |first1=Anita |title=Epix Greenlights Podcast-Inspired Docuseries \u2018Slow Burn\u2019 \u2013 TCA |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/epix-greenlights-podcast-inspired-docuseries-slow-burn-tca-1202553712/ |accessdate=16 December 2019 |publisher=Deadline}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\"Slow Burn\" to Premiere on EPIX(R) on February 16, 2020|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/11/20/slow-burn-to-premiere-on-epix-on-february-16-2020-96504/20191120epix01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=November 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Episodes===\n{{Episode table |background=#000000 |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |airdate= |airdateR=<ref name=\"TFC\">{{cite web |title=Slow Burn \u2013 Listings |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/slow-burn/listings/ |website=[[The Futon Critic]] |accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref>  |country=U.S. |viewers= |episodes= \n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Martha\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|16}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Losing Ground\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|23}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = Suspicious Minds\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|1}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |Title           = The Hearings\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|8}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |Title           = Smoking Gun\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|15}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |Title           = Massacre\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|22}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Epix}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n{{podcast-stub}}\n[[Category:2017 podcast debuts]]\n[[Category:Political podcasts]]\n[[Category:Works about the Watergate scandal]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Podcast}}\n{{Infobox podcast\n| show_name = Slow Burn\n| title = Slow Burn\n| image = Slow_Burn_podcast.jpg\n| format = {{hlist|[[History]]|[[Drama]]|Political Commentary}}\n| runtime = Typically 20 to 30 minutes\n| producer = Andrew Parsons\n| host = \n| starring = [[Leon Neyfakh]]\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| first_aired = November 28, 2017\n| num_episodes = {{plainlist|\n*Main series: 23<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|title=Slow Burn|url=https://slate.com/podcasts/slow-burn/s3/biggie-and-tupac|work=Slate Magazine}}</ref>\n*Bonus: 7}}\n| website = [https://slate.com/podcasts/slow-burn/s3/biggie-and-tupac] or visit [https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/slow-burn-a-podcast-about-watergate/id1315040130]\n}}\n'''''Slow Burn''''' is a narrative podcast produced by Slate Plus, a division of ''[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]].'' The first two seasons of the podcast are hosted by [[Leon Neyfakh]]<ref name=\"auto\" />; the third season of the show, released in 2019, is hosted by Joel Anderson<ref>{{Cite web|title='Slow Burn' Season 3 Turns Its Investigative Eye To The Murders Of Biggie And Tupac|url=https://www.npr.org/2019/11/07/776908450/slow-burn-season-3-turns-its-investigative-eye-to-the-murders-of-biggie-and-tupa|work=NPR.org|access-date=2019-11-17|language=en}}</ref>.\n\nThe first season is about the [[Watergate scandal]] featuring interviews with [[Bob Woodward]] among others.\n\nThe second is about the [[Impeachment of Bill Clinton]] featuring an interview with [[Linda Tripp]], among others.\n\nThe third season covers the growing tension between rappers [[Tupac Shakur]] and [[The Notorious B.I.G.|The Notorious B.I.G]]. in the 1990s<ref>{{Cite web|last=Anderson|first=Joel|title=Slow Burn|url=https://slate.com/podcasts/slow-burn/s3/biggie-and-tupac|work=Slate Magazine|date=2019-10-29|access-date=2019-11-17|language=en}}</ref>. \n\nThe podcast premiered on November 28, 2017 and became \"one of the top shows on Apple Podcasts.\"<ref name=\"usatoday.com\">{{cite web|title=Have you heard 'Slow Burn'? Slate's Watergate podcast is hot right now|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/12/02/slow-burn-slate-podcast-watergate/912144001/|work=}}</ref>\n\n==Reviews==\n''Slow Burn'' received a positive review from ''Vulture''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Slow Burn Is the Watergate Podcast You Didn\u2019t Know You Needed\n|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/01/podcast-review-slow-burn.html|accessdate=2019-12-16}}</ref> ''USA Today'' named ''Slow Burn'' as a \"hot\" recommended podcast.<ref name=\"usatoday.com\"/> ''The New York Times'' praised ''Slow Burn'' and credited [[Malcolm Gladwell]] with leading the way by making historic podcasts that focused on neglected aspects of well known events, like ''Slow Burn'', possible.<ref>{{cite web|title=Archived copy|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/15/arts/podcasts-revisionist-history-malcolm-gladwell.html/|accessdate=2018-02-04|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180203070053/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/15/arts/podcasts-revisionist-history-malcolm-gladwell.html|archivedate=2018-02-03}}</ref>\n\n==TV adaption==\nIt was announced in February 2019 that [[Epix]] is producing a six-part television series based on the first season Watergate investigation. It premiered on February 16, 2020.<ref>https://www.theverge.com/2019/2/10/18219436/epix-slate-slow-burn-podcast-documentary-series</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bennett |first1=Anita |title=Epix Greenlights Podcast-Inspired Docuseries \u2018Slow Burn\u2019 \u2013 TCA |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/epix-greenlights-podcast-inspired-docuseries-slow-burn-tca-1202553712/ |accessdate=16 December 2019 |publisher=Deadline}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\"Slow Burn\" to Premiere on EPIX(R) on February 16, 2020|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/11/20/slow-burn-to-premiere-on-epix-on-february-16-2020-96504/20191120epix01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=November 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Episodes===\n{{Episode table |background=#000000 |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |airdate= |airdateR=<ref name=\"TFC\">{{cite web |title=Slow Burn \u2013 Listings |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/slow-burn/listings/ |website=[[The Futon Critic]] |accessdate=February 16, 2020}}</ref>  |country=U.S. |viewers= |episodes= \n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Martha\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|16}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Losing Ground\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|23}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = Suspicious Minds\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|1}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |Title           = The Hearings\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|8}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |Title           = Smoking Gun\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|15}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |Title           = Massacre\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|22}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Epix}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n{{podcast-stub}}\n[[Category:2017 podcast debuts]]\n[[Category:Political podcasts]]\n[[Category:Works about the Wa